    {
      "content": "The health aggregation algorithm uses health policies that specify how to evaluate health reports as well as how to aggregate children health states (when applicable).",
      "pos": [
        15384,
        15551
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Health reports aggregation",
      "pos": [
        15557,
        15583
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "One entity can have multiple health reports sent by different reporters (system components or watchdogs) on different properties.",
      "pos": [
        15584,
        15713
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The aggregation uses the associated health policies, in particular the ConsiderWarningAsError member of application or cluster health policy, which specifies how to evaluate warnings.",
      "pos": [
        15714,
        15897
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The aggregated health state is triggered by the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>worst<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> health reports on the entity.",
      "pos": [
        15899,
        15986
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If there is at least one Error health report, the aggregated health state is Error.",
      "pos": [
        15987,
        16070
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Health Report Aggregation with Error Report.",
      "pos": [
        16074,
        16118
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Error health report triggers the health entity to be in Error state.",
      "pos": [
        16124,
        16192
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If there are no Error reports, and one or more Warning, the aggregated health state is either Warning or Error, depending on the ConsiderWarningAsError policy flag.",
      "pos": [
        16286,
        16450
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Health Report Aggregation with Warning Report and ConsiderWarningAsError false.",
      "pos": [
        16454,
        16533
      ]
    },
