      "pos": [
        23095,
        23183
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "IsExpired: flag to indicate whether the report was expired at the time the query was executed by the Health Store.",
      "pos": [
        23187,
        23301
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An event can be expired only if RemoveWhenExpired is false; otherwise, the event is not returned by query, it is removed from store.",
      "pos": [
        23302,
        23434
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "LastOkTransitionAt, LastWarningTransitionAt, LastErrorTransitionAt: last time for Ok/Warning/Error transitions.",
      "pos": [
        23438,
        23549
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "These fields give the history of the transition of the health states for the event.",
      "pos": [
        23550,
        23633
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The state transition fields can be used for smarter alerting or \"historical\" health event information.",
      "pos": [
        23635,
        23737
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "They enable scenarios like:",
      "pos": [
        23738,
        23765
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Alert when a property has been at Warning/Error for more than X minutes.",
      "pos": [
        23769,
        23841
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This avoids alerting on temporary conditions.",
      "pos": [
        23842,
        23887
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Eg: alert if the health state has been Warning for more than 5 minutes can be translated into (HealthState == Warning and Now - LastWarningTransitionTime",
      "pos": [
        23888,
        24041
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "5 minutes).",
      "pos": [
        24044,
        24055
      ]
    },
    {
